# =====================================================
# AL FRESCO CAFE POS SYSTEM - SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =====================================================
#
# This file is for reference only. No .env file is required to run the app.
# The Supabase credentials are pre-configured in the codebase.
#
# =====================================================
# QUICK START (VSCode)
# =====================================================
#
# 1. Open the project folder in VSCode
# 2. Open terminal (Ctrl+` or View > Terminal)
# 3. Run: npm install
# 4. Run: npm run dev
# 5. Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser
#
# =====================================================
# DATABASE SETUP (REQUIRED BEFORE FIRST RUN)
# =====================================================
# 
# Before using the app, run these SQL scripts in your Supabase SQL Editor:
#
# 1. scripts/create-database.sql - Creates users, products, orders tables
# 2. scripts/create-otp-table.sql - Creates OTP table for email verification  
# 3. scripts/add-void-key.sql - Creates admin_settings table for void key
#
# To access the SQL Editor:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project (or the pre-configured one)
# 3. Go to SQL Editor
# 4. Paste and run each script in order
#
# =====================================================
# OPTIONAL: Use your own Supabase project
# =====================================================
#
# If you want to use your own Supabase project, update these files:
# - lib/supabase/client.ts
# - lib/supabase/server.ts
#
# Replace SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY with your project credentials
# from your Supabase dashboard > Settings > API
